	Sales Analysis. 
	The Siam Pan Group Public Company Limited reported sales of 3.27 billion Thai Bahts (US$98.35 million)
		for the
		
		year ending
		December of 2016.
	
		This
		
			represents
		
			a
			
			decrease of 3.3%
		
		 versus 2015, when the company's sales were 3.39 billion Thai Bahts.
	
		The sales level in 2016 was fairly close to the level five years ago: in 2011, The Siam Pan Group Public Company Limited had sales
		of 3.25 billion Thai Bahts.
	
		Contributing to the drop in overall sales was the 12.7% decline
		in Batteries, from 758.95 million Thai Bahts to 662.60 million Thai Bahts.
		
					There were also decreases in sales in
					Grease (down 1.7% to 954.33 million Thai Bahts)
				
					and
				Others (down 2.1% to 37.20 million Thai Bahts)
				.
		
					However, these declines were partially offset by the increase in sales of
					Lubricating Oil (up 0.1% to 1.62 billion Thai Bahts)
				
			.
		

	




 


 
 


 
 


 
 











 



 













 










